                        <provenance type="found" when="1867">Discovered and identified by William Williams in 1867, but the ogham inscriptions were not fully read until the souterrain was dismantled in 1936 (Macalister 1945, 267). One of ten ogham stones used in the construction of the souterrain - five as lintels, which are now removed and placed upright beside the souterrain, and five as lining stones for the sides, which are still in position. This is the first lintel which was over the entrance of the souterrain.
